              "code": "A1",
              "type": "A",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "$336x^2 - 2240x^3$"
            }
          ],
          "guidance": "Note that a correct expression scores 4/4\nM1: Correct form for $x^2$ or $x^3$. Look for the correct binomial coefficient with the correct power of x. You do not need to be concerned with the $4^-$ which may have been omitted.\nAllow alternative equivalent notation for the binomial coefficient for this mark e.g. $^7C_2$ or $^7C_5$ or $\\binom{7}{2}$ or $7!/(2!5!)$ etc\nCondone invisible brackets for this mark e.g. $^7C_2 4x^2$\nA1: Correct $x^2$ or $x^3$ term (which may be unsimplified). They must have a numerical expression or value for their binomial coefficient for this mark. i.e. do not allow e.g. $^7C_3$\nDo not condone poor bracketing for this mark but may be implied by further work.\nB1: For the series starting $1 - 28x$ (terms may be in any order or as a list)\nCondone $1 + (-28x)$ but not e.g. $1 - 28x^+$\nisw if they subsequently incorrectly attempt to simplify their answer.\nA1: $336x^2 - 2240x^3$ Do not accept e.g. $336x^2 + (-2240x^3)$ unless already penalised for B1.\nAllow the terms to be written as a list.\nisw once the correct simplified terms have been found"
        },
        {
          "label": "(b)",
          "marks": 2,
          "answer": "k = 13",
          "markAllocation": [
            {
              "code": "M1",
              "type": "M",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "Sets \"336\" - 5 \"28\"k = 1316"
            },
            {
              "code": "A1",
              "type": "A",
              "value": 1,
              "criterion": "k = 13"
            }
          ],
          "guidance": "M1: Adds the correct two terms using their coefficients from (a) and sets equal to 1316. (Allow misread)\nLook for ''336'' $\\pm$ 5 ''28''k = 1316 i.e. they do not need to proceed to a value for k for this mark\nIf they still have x and $x^2$ present in the equation then these must be removed or implied by further work to score the mark. Condone transcription errors from their part (a).\nIf just a value is stated following an incorrect part (a), then you will need to check this.\nA1: k = 13"
        }
      ]
